        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 2:22PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 222 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Jena, or 10 miles southwest of Northport, moving south at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Romulus, Fosters, Ralph, and Fosters Boat Landing.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
